## Proposed Changes

### Database

#### [NEW] `peer_review_migration.sql`

Creates `review_cycles` and `peer_reviews` tables, RPC for submitting reviews, and updates `recent_changes_view` to include peer review activity.

Key columns:
- `peer_reviews.rubric_version` — stores `'v1'` so historical reviews stay valid when rubric is revised
- `peer_reviews.aligned_with_outcome` — set to `true`/`false` after cycle closes, drives alignment feedback
- `peer_reviews.criteria_scores` — JSONB: `{ "legal_accuracy": "pass", "clarity": "needs_work", ... }`
- `review_cycles.target_tier` — only `'good_article'` or `'featured'`
- `review_cycles.outcome` — `'advanced'` / `'maintained'` / `'split'` / null (while open)

RLS:
- `peer_reviews` readable by everyone AFTER cycle closes (prevents anchoring during open cycles)
- While cycle is open, reviewers can only see their own review
- Authenticated users can insert

